thread.title: Tropical Storm Marty weakens a little of Mexico’s coast

title: Tropical Storm Marty weakens a little of Mexico’s coast
text:
MIAMI (AP) — Tropical Storm Marty has weakened a little off Mexico’s Pacific coast.
The storm’s maximum sustained winds early Tuesday decreased to near 65 mph (100 kph) with additional weakening expected over the next few days.
Marty is centered about 90 miles (145 kilometers) south of Zihuatanejo, Mexico, and is moving east near 2 mph (4 kph). A tropical storm warning is in effect for part of Mexico’s coast from Acapulco to Lazaro Cardenas.
Meanwhile in the Atlantic, Tropical Storm Joaquin is expected to slowly strengthen over the next two days.
